# No UTF-8 BOM

Agent Skills validators and this repo's `update_skills_index.py` require frontmatter to start with `---` at byte 0. A UTF-8 BOM (`EF BB BF` / `U+FEFF`) before `---` makes otherwise-valid `SKILL.md` files fail install and indexing.

## Rules

1. **Never write a UTF-8 BOM** when creating or editing text files in this repo (`SKILL.md`, `references/*.md`, `.gd`, `.py`, `.json`, `.mdc`, configs, etc.).
2. **Save as UTF-8 without BOM.** On Windows especially, do not use "UTF-8 with signature."
3. **If you see a BOM**, strip it before committing. First three bytes must not be `EF BB BF`.
4. **Python I/O**: read with `encoding="utf-8-sig"` when parsing may encounter legacy BOM; write with `encoding="utf-8"` (no BOM).
5. Prefer editing tools/APIs that do not prepend BOM. After bulk text rewrites, spot-check a `SKILL.md` by reading the first 3-4 bytes.

## Quick check

```powershell
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -File skills | ForEach-Object {
  $b = [IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($_.FullName)
  if ($b.Length -ge 3 -and $b[0]-eq 0xEF -and $b[1]-eq 0xBB -and $b[2]-eq 0xBF) { $_.FullName }
}
```

## Why this matters

BOM on `SKILL.md` frontmatter caused silent install rejection. Do not reintroduce it.
